class LUPrefix {
public:
    LUPrefix(int n) : videos(n + 1, false), maxUploaded(0) {}

    void upload(int video) {
        videos[video] = true;
        while (maxUploaded + 1 < videos.size() && videos[++maxUploaded]);
    }

    int longest() {
        return maxUploaded;
    }

private:
    vector<bool> videos;
    int maxUploaded;
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: 
- LUPrefix: O(n)
- upload: O(1) amortized
- longest: O(1)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses a boolean vector to track uploaded videos and an integer to store the length of the longest uploaded prefix. The upload function updates the vector and increments the prefix length as necessary. The longest function simply returns the current prefix length.

